It's important to find someone

07:02.219 --> 07:03.753
that you can kind of forget
is there

07:03.755 --> 07:06.322
so that when they leave,
it's like losing a cat.

07:06.324 --> 07:08.224
No, that... that's not
exactly what I..

07:08.226 --> 07:09.859
You know,
I... I need to be careful.

07:09.861 --> 07:11.960
I need someone
I can picture in sweatpants

07:11.962 --> 07:13.630
just the right amount of mousy.

07:13.632 --> 07:16.765
Do you listen
to the Modern Love podcast?

07:16.767 --> 07:19.335
- I don't. You do?
- Religiously.

07:19.337 --> 07:21.570
There was a story the other day
about a couple

07:21.572 --> 07:23.505
where he was deaf
and she was blind

07:23.507 --> 07:26.075
so they couldn't speak
or use sign language

07:26.077 --> 07:28.411
but they were happily married
for, like, 15 years.

07:28.413 --> 07:31.448
- Mm-hmm. What happened then?
- Oh.

07:31.450 --> 07:34.017
She was killed
by a self-driving car.

07:34.019 --> 07:37.286
- Yeah. It was a lot.
- Thanks for your input, Victor.

07:37.288 --> 07:40.423
Everyone stop talking right now.
I need to concentrate.

07:40.425 --> 07:42.224
You don't have to react
that way to stuff.

07:42.226 --> 07:43.359
Like with my mom
with the baseball..

07:43.361 --> 07:44.661
I took you
to the baseball game.

07:44.663 --> 07:47.130
You were like a crazy person
at the baseball game.

07:47.132 --> 07:49.666
A crazy person at a ba..
It's a baseball game.

07:49.668 --> 07:51.433
Is there etiquette
for a baseball game?

07:51.435 --> 07:53.335
It's a Little League game
with kids. Alright?

07:53.337 --> 07:54.871
Okay, fine.
So how about you getting drunk

07:54.873 --> 07:56.138
at a Little League game?

07:56.140 --> 07:58.474
Well, what else are you gonna do
at a Little League game?

07:58.476 --> 08:00.510
I want you to sit down
for a second.

08:12.123 --> 08:14.791
I ask you to..
I ask you to relax.

08:14.793 --> 08:16.592
I say, "Relax,"
and you take it...

08:16.594 --> 08:20.162
It is the most annoying thing
on the planet to hear.

08:20.164 --> 08:22.498
I'm just saying relax,
like it's not that big...

08:22.500 --> 08:25.734
- Stop saying that.
- Will you just relax?

08:25.736 --> 08:27.402
What are they talking about?

08:27.404 --> 08:30.940
You know I've been doing a lot
of work on myself lately.

08:30.942 --> 08:33.909
Like, I've really been trying
to become a better person.

08:33.910 --> 08:36.846
Are you breaking up with me?

08:36.847 --> 08:38.948
- Yes.
- Seriously?

08:38.950 --> 08:40.784
- Shh.
- Shh.

08:40.785 --> 08:43.054
We're in a library.

08:45.123 --> 08:48.824
Is that why you brought me here?
So I wouldn't raise my voice?

08:48.826 --> 08:50.959
- <i>Shh.</i>
- <i>No.</i>

08:50.961 --> 08:53.730
Listen,
we both know that you're passionate.

08:53.732 --> 08:55.564
Oh, is that a euphemism
for loud?

08:55.566 --> 08:57.132
- <i>Shh.</i>
- It's gettin' heated.

08:57.134 --> 08:58.934
Euphemism's a great word.

08:58.936 --> 09:01.571
Here's another one.
You're freakin' bananas.

09:01.573 --> 09:04.039
- Motherfuck!
- Ow! Alright.

09:04.041 --> 09:06.976
- Great.
- Are you serious right now?

09:06.978 --> 09:09.044
- Ugh! Take that!
- Okay, ma'am, would you mind?

09:09.046 --> 09:11.481
- Miss?
- Will you, please, get down?

09:11.483 --> 09:13.917
- I like it up here.
- Yeah, she's crazy, man.

09:13.919 --> 09:16.052
And not just like part of the
month, like the whole thing.

09:16.054 --> 09:19.856
Oh, my God! This penny loafer
wearing asshole

09:19.858 --> 09:21.558
brought me in here
to break up with me.

09:21.560 --> 09:23.659
Yeah, 'cause I thought
she'd keep a lid on it for once.

09:23.661 --> 09:25.595
- Ugh!
- Excuse me. Excuse me.

09:25.597 --> 09:29.031
- Why don't you just let it out?
- What?

09:29.033 --> 09:30.399
You're standing on a table

09:30.401 --> 09:31.668
you clearly
have something to say.

09:31.670 --> 09:34.236
I think you should say it.

09:34.238 --> 09:37.640
Okay, well, for example,
"Keep a lid on it."

09:37.642 --> 09:39.675
I don't have to keep a lid
on anything.

09:39.677 --> 09:42.544
I'm pretty sure every nerd
in this library disagrees.

09:42.546 --> 09:43.746
<i>You know what's crazy is</i>

09:43.748 --> 09:46.082
I don't even know
how we ended up together.

09:46.084 --> 09:49.751
He's... he's rude to waiters.
He screens calls from his mom.

09:49.753 --> 09:52.755
- He threads his eyebrows.
- I'm part Greek.

09:52.757 --> 09:53.823
And your friends don't like him?

09:53.825 --> 09:55.524
Oh, they hate him.

09:55.526 --> 09:57.492
And they can't understand
what I see in him, you know.

09:57.494 --> 09:59.895
And then after a while

09:59.897 --> 10:01.997
it becomes the reason
why I'm with him.

10:01.999 --> 10:05.434
Sure. It's bad choices.
That's your thing, right?

10:05.436 --> 10:08.103
- Yeah. So it's her fault.
- Hey, hey.

10:08.105 --> 10:10.305
Miss, please,
give Lavelle the book.

10:10.307 --> 10:12.408
You stand back
or I'm gonna tear this apart.

10:12.410 --> 10:14.343
She's all talk.

10:14.345 --> 10:15.645
Ma'am?

10:15.647 --> 10:18.014
- Ma'am?
- Ugh!

10:18.016 --> 10:19.548
Ma'am!

10:19.550 --> 10:22.217
You will never ever tear
the binding on that book.

10:22.219 --> 10:25.154
It's reinforced for libraries.

10:25.156 --> 10:27.323
You can, however, try the pages.

10:27.325 --> 10:28.457
- Charlie?
- No, no, please.

10:28.459 --> 10:30.092
Start in the middle.
Knock yourself out.

10:30.094 --> 10:31.627
- Okay. Yeah!
- There you go!

10:31.629 --> 10:33.228
See how good that feels?

10:33.230 --> 10:34.797
- Ooh!
- Does that feel good?

10:34.799 --> 10:37.366
- Huh? Am I being loud now?
- Just relax.

10:37.368 --> 10:39.269
Oh, relax?

10:39.271 --> 10:40.470
<i>Relax?</i>

10:40.472 --> 10:42.605
Re.. Re..

10:42.607 --> 10:44.009
Relax!

10:47.512 --> 10:49.345
- Ooh!
- <i>Tell me something.</i>

10:50.916 --> 10:54.250
Did you ever really think
that this would last?

10:54.252 --> 10:56.752
<i>Or, uh, the better question is</i>

10:56.754 --> 10:58.954
did you ever really want it to?

11:07.998 --> 11:09.667
Fine, we can break up.

11:11.969 --> 11:13.973
Well, that went as expected.

11:16.074 --> 11:17.906
- Thanks.
- <i>How'd he do that?</i>

11:17.908 --> 11:20.076
Like a blind man
learns to listen

11:20.078 --> 11:22.047
except Charlie's got an ear
for pain.

11:24.950 --> 11:26.582
- What's it to you?
- What?

11:26.584 --> 11:28.384
Uh, I'm... I'm just..

11:28.386 --> 11:30.986
I'm trying to keep things
calm here.

11:30.988 --> 11:32.925
- You're good at it.
- I need to be.

11:34.792 --> 11:37.095
- Sorry!
- Don't do that anymore.

11:41.498 --> 11:42.966
I'm taking off early.

11:42.968 --> 11:45.968
Measles outbreak on the rise.
CDC concerned.

11:45.970 --> 11:47.202
Thank you.

12:03.688 --> 12:05.321
Zika virus.

12:05.323 --> 12:07.222
Congress.

12:07.224 --> 12:08.658
Oh, God.

12:08.660 --> 12:10.459
Famine in Darfur.

12:10.461 --> 12:11.861
White guy, dreadlocks.

12:11.863 --> 12:13.496
Oh!

12:13.498 --> 12:14.896
- Hey, Charlie.
- Hey.

12:14.898 --> 12:17.632
- You just made it.
- Barely.

12:17.634 --> 12:18.836
Thanks.

12:24.709 --> 12:27.043
- <i>You good?</i>
- Yeah.

13:02.613 --> 13:05.715
There's someone here to see you.
She brought you something.

13:05.717 --> 13:06.852
She?

13:08.619 --> 13:10.520
Oh, God. Tell her I died.

13:10.522 --> 13:12.221
I already told her
you were here.

13:12.223 --> 13:13.755
- It was a very sudden...
- Hello?

13:13.757 --> 13:15.191
Hi there, Mr. Librarian.

13:15.193 --> 13:17.129
Hey. Come to throw
more books around?

13:18.595 --> 13:22.298
I'm here to thank you for coming
to my defense the other day.

13:22.300 --> 13:23.765
Oh, I... I didn't come
to your defense.

13:23.767 --> 13:26.034
I... I just came to get you
off the table.

13:26.036 --> 13:27.837
Well, still, I appreciate it.

13:27.839 --> 13:30.472
I, uh, I got you this.
A replacement.

13:30.474 --> 13:33.308
- Didn't have to do that.
- It's the least I could do.

13:33.310 --> 13:34.976
No, the copy you destroyed
was a first edition.

13:34.978 --> 13:36.111
Oh.

13:36.113 --> 13:38.014
Oh, I'm sorry.

13:38.016 --> 13:39.548
Well, you did kind of
egg me on though.

13:39.550 --> 13:41.320
Oh.

13:42.520 --> 13:43.689
Alright.

13:45.355 --> 13:47.189
I was thinking about something
you said that day.

13:47.191 --> 13:48.390
Right.

13:48.392 --> 13:49.792
Uh, did I really
want it to last

13:49.794 --> 13:51.026
and I realized that I didn't.

13:51.028 --> 13:52.395
It's a good thing it ended then.

13:52.397 --> 13:54.163
Yeah, but why did I
get into a relationship

13:54.165 --> 13:55.331
I knew was doomed to fail?

13:55.333 --> 13:56.933
Ask the guy who doomed it.

13:56.935 --> 13:58.333
It's not his fault.

13:58.335 --> 14:01.303
Actually, it is all his fault.

14:01.305 --> 14:02.605
But I knew where it was headed

14:02.607 --> 14:05.173
when he canceled on a date
to go to a boat show.

14:05.175 --> 14:07.043
By the way, he's the second guy
to do that to me.

14:07.045 --> 14:08.914
Maybe you should move inland?

14:10.248 --> 14:12.180
There's something
I find irresistible about men

14:12.182 --> 14:13.249
I have no future with.

14:15.887 --> 14:16.952
Oh.

14:21.291 --> 14:22.524
Right.

14:22.526 --> 14:24.393
It's so quiet in here.

14:24.395 --> 14:25.394
Does it make you
just wanna scream?

14:25.396 --> 14:26.529
Don't scream, please.

14:27.665 --> 14:29.499
Come on, have you tried
screaming? It's fun.

14:29.501 --> 14:31.867
I know it's fun, but there's
more to life than fun, you know.

14:31.869 --> 14:34.472
- Is there?
- I'm not sure anymore.

14:40.277 --> 14:42.678
Well, uh, thanks again.

14:42.680 --> 14:45.050
- I'm Francesca, by the way.
- I'm Charlie.

14:51.522 --> 14:54.390
Well, um, it was nice
to meet you, too, Charlie.

14:54.392 --> 14:56.027
Yeah. Uh..

14:57.060 --> 14:58.296
Yeah.

15:00.098 --> 15:02.999
We need to settle something
right now.

15:03.001 --> 15:04.366
Are you gay?

15:04.368 --> 15:07.436
I mean, it's... it's cool
if you are, but I gotta know

15:07.438 --> 15:09.938
'cause I want off
this emotional rollercoaster.

15:09.940 --> 15:12.241
I'm not gay, Lavelle.

15:12.243 --> 15:14.076
Eunuch? Are you a eunuch?

15:14.078 --> 15:15.477
- What?
- It is unfair.

15:15.479 --> 15:17.513
You won't go out with her
because of how she looks.

15:17.515 --> 15:19.215
It's not her fault
that she's smoking hot.

15:19.217 --> 15:21.016
No, it's not just her looks.
It's her manner.

15:21.018 --> 15:23.619
It's her laugh. It's her
stupid gift-wrapped books.

15:23.621 --> 15:26.154
She's just too..

15:26.156 --> 15:27.923
Too.

15:27.925 --> 15:29.759
It sounds like
you kind of dig her.

15:29.761 --> 15:30.959
That's the problem.

15:30.961 --> 15:32.962
<i>Let's get down to brass tacks,
Charlie.</i>

15:32.964 --> 15:36.131
Sperm quality declines sharply
after age 35.

15:36.133 --> 15:38.000
Thank you, Victor.

15:38.002 --> 15:40.602
You gotta stick your neck out
sometime, Charlie.

15:40.604 --> 15:43.207
- Life will pass you right by.
- Yeah, right.

15:48.979 --> 15:50.114
Okay!

15:52.450 --> 15:53.982
Okay, what?

15:53.984 --> 15:56.954
Okay, I'll go out with you.

15:58.388 --> 16:01.856
Oh, I, I didn't exactly ask.

16:01.858 --> 16:04.659
Uh, how does
2 o'clock Saturday sound?

16:04.661 --> 16:07.730
- Will your mom be driving?
- My parents are dead.

16:07.732 --> 16:08.867
Oh.

16:11.536 --> 16:14.370
Okay then.
Saturday at 2:00.

16:14.372 --> 16:16.404
- I'll wear sunscreen.
- Great.

16:16.406 --> 16:19.308
I mean, good.
S... see you then.

16:19.310 --> 16:21.143
Oh, wait. Charlie,
don't you need my number?

16:21.145 --> 16:24.583
Call the front desk later.
I need to go right now.

16:29.820 --> 16:32.321
I don't know.
I guess I just don't get it.

16:32.323 --> 16:35.024
You haven't gone on a date
in years, right?

16:35.026 --> 16:37.963
- So why her? Why now?
- I don't know.

16:39.229 --> 16:40.730
She was so angry.

16:40.732 --> 16:43.131
Beside herself.
Completely out of control.

16:43.133 --> 16:46.334
- It was thrilling.
- Uff. I don't get that at all.

16:46.336 --> 16:48.537
It's like she's everything
I've ever avoided.

16:48.539 --> 16:51.810
- I'm drawn to her like a moth.
- To a flame.

16:53.844 --> 16:56.345
Charlie, the end of that phrase
is to a burning, deadly flame.

16:56.347 --> 16:57.783
Yeah, I... I get it.

16:58.950 --> 17:00.515
What is there to decide?

17:00.517 --> 17:03.084
All your shirts look the same.

17:03.086 --> 17:05.320
Why do all your shirts
look the same?

17:05.323 --> 17:06.592
No compliments.

17:08.226 --> 17:10.892
Does she know?
Does Francesca...

17:10.894 --> 17:12.560
Are you kidding?
Hi, I'm Charlie.

17:12.563 --> 17:13.963
I'm medically forbidden
to have fun.

17:13.964 --> 17:15.630
You wanna go out?

17:15.632 --> 17:17.365
Pass the tacks.

17:17.367 --> 17:18.633
No.

17:18.635 --> 17:20.769
Come on, Charlie.
It's too gruesome.

17:20.771 --> 17:22.737
It works.

17:22.739 --> 17:24.442
Fine.

17:25.575 --> 17:27.575
Listen, you put
as many office supplies

17:27.577 --> 17:29.111
in the bottom of your shoe
as you want.

17:29.113 --> 17:32.113
Eventually,
she's gonna find out.

17:32.115 --> 17:34.051
Dates are supposed to be fun.

17:35.819 --> 17:37.421
Not this one.

17:39.457 --> 17:42.591
The only good thing to come
of my grandmother's Alzheimer's

17:42.593 --> 17:46.565
was that it helped her forget
her miserable life.

17:47.931 --> 17:51.766
She was raised in a Hooverville

17:51.768 --> 17:54.637
on the wrong side
of the wrong side of the tracks.

17:54.639 --> 17:57.073
The kind of place
where dreams go to die

17:57.075 --> 18:01.476
and hope,
hope is smothered

18:01.478 --> 18:03.446
in its crib.

18:03.448 --> 18:04.714
- Is he a friend of yours?
- No.

18:04.716 --> 18:07.749
See Mildred Munch
didn't have hope.

18:07.751 --> 18:10.186
She didn't have dreams

18:10.188 --> 18:13.825
so she didn't have
nothing to lose.

18:18.095 --> 18:21.030
Norman, you son of a bitch.
You get a job.

18:21.032 --> 18:24.367
You get a job
or you're gonna get a new wife.

18:24.369 --> 18:27.669
Those are empty threats, just
like you're an empty person..

18:27.671 --> 18:29.804
Were there good reviews?

18:29.806 --> 18:30.973
I didn't check.

18:30.975 --> 18:32.707
You're not a man,
you're a hulk.

18:34.112 --> 18:35.111
No, please, I..

18:36.146 --> 18:37.580
Why not?

18:37.582 --> 18:40.783
<i>And that, dear friends,
is when Mildred Munch</i>

18:40.785 --> 18:44.690
my Bubbie Millie turned..

18:45.690 --> 18:47.555
...to prostitution.

18:50.862 --> 18:52.695
Hand jobs!

18:52.697 --> 18:54.662
Seriously, why are we here?

18:54.664 --> 18:56.297
- Hand jobs! First one's free!
- Huh?

18:56.299 --> 18:58.167
Why are we here?

18:58.169 --> 18:59.802
- <i>Shh.</i>
- I'm sorry.

18:59.804 --> 19:02.772
Is my play interrupting
your conversation?

19:02.774 --> 19:04.140
No.

19:04.142 --> 19:06.574
'Cause I didn't buy a ticket
to your conversation.

19:06.576 --> 19:08.677
- So sorry. We, we're done.
- Yeah.

19:08.679 --> 19:10.579
- We're.. Uh, please, continue.
- Sorry.

19:10.581 --> 19:13.248
Thank you for permission
to continue my play, sir.

19:13.250 --> 19:15.251
I very much appreciate it.

19:15.253 --> 19:17.119
I'll just hop back
into the moment..

19:17.121 --> 19:19.021
We should go. I'm sorry.

19:19.023 --> 19:20.322
...I'll just pretend
that I'm not

19:20.324 --> 19:21.457
completely distracted right now.

19:21.459 --> 19:22.457
I'm sorry.

19:22.459 --> 19:23.825
How about I skip
to the part where

19:23.827 --> 19:26.762
uh, her first-born dies
of common diarrhea?

19:26.764 --> 19:28.367
I said diarrhea!

19:30.634 --> 19:34.004
I said diarrhea.

19:36.140 --> 19:38.774
- Diarrhea!
- Alright. Yeah.

19:38.776 --> 19:39.941
I... I know.

19:39.943 --> 19:42.044
I know, but to be fair to him

19:42.046 --> 19:43.711
we did kind of...

19:43.713 --> 19:46.282
- Diarrhea?
- Yeah, diarrhea.

19:46.284 --> 19:48.453
Look, I kind of feel for him.

19:50.086 --> 19:52.822
- Where are we?
- Uh, it's, uh..

19:52.824 --> 19:54.989
Are we, are we in danger?

19:54.991 --> 19:57.192
Oh, it's starting to feel
that way, yeah.

19:57.194 --> 19:59.495
Hold onto me,
so you don't get kidnapped.

20:04.469 --> 20:06.634
So tell me about your sick aunt.

20:06.636 --> 20:08.970
Wow, you flirt weird.

20:08.972 --> 20:11.873
Sorry.

20:11.875 --> 20:14.677
It seemed important. It's
something you're going through.

20:14.679 --> 20:16.911
Yeah, sometimes it's nice
not to be going through it.

20:16.913 --> 20:18.447
Yeah, of course, it is,
but I'm an idiot

20:18.449 --> 20:20.384
so just ignore me.
You'll have way more fun.

20:21.419 --> 20:22.517
It's alright.

20:22.519 --> 20:24.455
Since we're on the subject..

20:25.456 --> 20:27.656
...it is hard.

20:27.658 --> 20:28.858
She's like my second mother

20:28.860 --> 20:31.826
after my real mother died
of the same thing.

20:31.828 --> 20:34.095
Breast cancer runs in my family
like hammertoes.

20:34.097 --> 20:37.168
So... I've got that
to look forward to.

20:38.401 --> 20:40.736
Look who's being fun now.

20:40.738 --> 20:43.374
I'm sorry, Francesca.
That's awful.

20:44.875 --> 20:46.010
Thank you.

20:48.211 --> 20:50.478
It's not all bad. I've gotten
really close with Sylvia

20:50.480 --> 20:52.448
since I've been living with her

20:52.450 --> 20:54.550
which I guess means
it's gonna hurt

20:54.552 --> 20:56.755
that much more when she, um..

20:58.855 --> 21:01.323
Well, that will burn New York
for me.

21:01.325 --> 21:02.957
Are you gonna leave?

21:02.959 --> 21:05.363
Oh, yeah. But I always do.

21:08.598 --> 21:11.900
I lost somebody close to me
when I was young.

21:11.902 --> 21:15.437
My Grandpa Jacob, he was like
my best friend growing up.

21:15.439 --> 21:19.475
We had the same, uh..
We had a lot in common.

21:19.477 --> 21:21.709
Every Sunday, he'd take me out
to the carousel

21:21.711 --> 21:24.880
let me go round and round
as many times as I wanted

21:24.882 --> 21:28.149
even after he had to stop,
you know.

21:28.151 --> 21:30.622
I think that's the happiest
that I've ever been.

21:33.457 --> 21:35.093
Are you happy now?

21:37.961 --> 21:40.696
Not as happy as Mildred Munch.

21:40.698 --> 21:41.999
Diarrhea.

21:43.500 --> 21:45.167
- Common diarrhea.
- Common.

21:45.169 --> 21:47.669
- Not even special diarrhea.
- Nope, common.

21:47.671 --> 21:49.705
- You didn't have one.
- Exactly.

21:49.707 --> 21:50.906
On the wrong side
of the wrong side of the tracks.

21:50.908 --> 21:53.309
The wrong side of the wrong side
of the tracks.

21:53.311 --> 21:54.610
Like Troy McClure.

21:54.612 --> 21:56.477
I can't believe
you took me to that play.

21:56.479 --> 21:57.646
Nor can I.

21:57.648 --> 21:59.547
This is me.

21:59.549 --> 22:01.316
So, uh, my aunt
should still be at karate

22:01.318 --> 22:03.485
if you wanna come up
for a drink.

22:03.487 --> 22:05.588
A drink? It's 3:30.

22:05.590 --> 22:08.023
Yes, it is.

22:08.025 --> 22:09.960
It's not about the drink,
Charlie.

22:17.701 --> 22:19.435
Sure, why not?

22:19.437 --> 22:21.102
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

22:21.104 --> 22:23.805
You know, I see now
why you insisted on a matinee.

22:23.807 --> 22:25.841
We have more energy
for messin' around.

22:31.282 --> 22:32.715
Char... Charlie?

22:32.717 --> 22:35.117
Oh, my God. Charlie!

22:35.119 --> 22:37.352
Charlie!

22:53.437 --> 22:54.805
Oh, come on.

22:56.507 --> 22:58.506
<i>Excuse me. Excuse me. Hi.</i>

22:58.508 --> 23:00.441
Uh, I'm looking
for, uh, Charles Greene.

23:00.443 --> 23:02.544
Are you here for Charlie?

23:02.546 --> 23:04.045
I'm Francesca.

23:04.047 --> 23:06.681
Oh, Jesus. No wonder.

23:06.683 --> 23:08.082
Sorry.

23:08.084 --> 23:10.419
Hi. Cooper, brother.

23:10.421 --> 23:12.454
Oh.

23:12.456 --> 23:13.656
So how'd it go?

23:13.658 --> 23:16.091
What do you mean?
We ended up here.

23:16.093 --> 23:17.659
Right.
Have you heard anything?

23:17.661 --> 23:19.294
Uh, just that
he didn't break his neck

23:19.296 --> 23:20.629
which I guess is good.

23:20.631 --> 23:23.631
Yeah. I guess you two
really hit it off, huh?

23:23.633 --> 23:25.801
Well, yeah. I mean, I think..
I thought so.

23:25.803 --> 23:27.769
I... I don't know.

23:27.771 --> 23:31.707
I mean, we were headed upstairs
and he just dropped.

23:31.709 --> 23:34.976
He, like, I think he fainted
from the heat or something?

23:34.978 --> 23:37.545
Yeah. Yep. From the heat.
Yeah, probably.

23:37.547 --> 23:39.380
You know, that's super common
because you gotta...

23:39.382 --> 23:41.216
Well, good news.

23:41.218 --> 23:43.185
Charlie's got
a pretty nasty cut

23:43.187 --> 23:44.687
and his head's gonna ache
for a while

23:44.689 --> 23:46.755
but there's no fractures,
so all in all

23:46.757 --> 23:48.424
we feel he got off lucky
this time.

23:48.426 --> 23:50.159
- This time?
- Yeah...

23:50.161 --> 23:53.562
You know what,
Charlie's, uh, got a thing.

23:53.564 --> 23:56.765
And it's a condition,
according to some

23:56.767 --> 23:58.600
but to others,
it's an adorable quirk.

23:58.602 --> 24:00.502
It's a disease likely caused

24:00.504 --> 24:02.603
by the shortage of hypocretin
in his brain.

24:02.605 --> 24:05.407
It's a chemical signal that
makes most of us stay awake.

24:05.409 --> 24:07.909
Essentially,
Charlie's body gets tricked

24:07.911 --> 24:10.746
to think that it's asleep.

24:10.748 --> 24:12.851
Well, adorable quirk.

24:14.151 --> 24:15.519
Disease.

24:21.691 --> 24:23.027
Hey.

24:24.495 --> 24:25.764
Oh, hi.

24:29.200 --> 24:32.400
So, that was crazy.

24:32.402 --> 24:34.836
I guess I must have fainted.
I need to hydrate.

24:34.838 --> 24:36.774
Charlie, I know.

24:44.681 --> 24:46.017
What's it called?

24:48.952 --> 24:51.320
Cataplexy.

24:51.322 --> 24:53.691
Technically,
narcolepsy with cataplexy.

24:55.492 --> 24:57.027
Runs in the family.

24:58.362 --> 25:00.394
Your Grampa Jacob?

25:00.396 --> 25:02.230
Yeah.

25:02.232 --> 25:03.931
Yeah.

25:03.933 --> 25:06.034
Growing up, I... I thought
he slept all the time

25:06.036 --> 25:07.902
'cause he was old

25:07.904 --> 25:10.872
and then it started
happening to me.

25:10.874 --> 25:14.612
<i>Pretty much any strong emotion
will trigger it.</i>

25:15.813 --> 25:17.582
In my case, it's..

25:19.682 --> 25:21.685
...it's mainly when I'm happy.

25:23.053 --> 25:24.456
<i>So thank you.</i>

25:28.325 --> 25:30.993
Why didn't you tell me?

25:30.995 --> 25:35.197
Uh, well, I had a girlfriend
in college

25:35.199 --> 25:38.036
Alice, and, uh, she knew.

25:40.171 --> 25:42.106
But she didn't really know,
you know.

25:44.642 --> 25:46.941
And because she was my first

25:46.943 --> 25:48.576
I didn't know
what would actually happen

25:48.578 --> 25:51.315
when we finally, um..

25:52.882 --> 25:54.949
Oh, when you..

25:54.951 --> 25:57.753
Oh! Oh, wow!

25:57.755 --> 25:59.254
That's, it's not funny.

25:59.256 --> 26:00.721
Oh, come on,
it's a little bit funny.

26:00.723 --> 26:02.490
- It's not at all..
- I mean, what..

26:02.492 --> 26:04.426
Not in the least bit funny.

26:04.428 --> 26:06.829
- I'm sorry.
- Jesus Christ.

26:06.831 --> 26:09.267
Okay. You're right.
It is not funny.

26:11.869 --> 26:15.336
You know,
I came to naked on my back..

26:15.338 --> 26:19.740
...surrounded by EMTs,
the RA, half the dorm.

26:19.742 --> 26:21.879
- Alice thought I'd died.
- Oh.

26:23.581 --> 26:27.983
I mostly steered clear
of girlfriends since then.

26:27.985 --> 26:29.921
I... I can't afford
the insurance.

26:33.591 --> 26:35.794
Today was a really big deal
for you, wasn't it?

26:39.462 --> 26:41.565
It was a really big deal
for me too.

26:43.433 --> 26:46.237
Remember I never date guys
I think I have a future with?

26:50.440 --> 26:52.807
Let's quit while we're ahead.

26:52.809 --> 26:55.177
I took a risk.
It was obviously a bad idea.

26:55.179 --> 26:56.745
Oh, hey, don't worry about it.

26:56.747 --> 26:59.480
We'll just take it slow.
We'll stick to really boring...

26:59.482 --> 27:00.549
It's not gonna work.

27:00.551 --> 27:02.383
Wait, like, um,
the botanical gardens...

27:02.385 --> 27:04.820
It's not gonna work.
It's not that simple.

27:04.822 --> 27:07.421
Symposiums, lectures,
Roosevelt Island...

27:07.423 --> 27:10.027
Please... stop.

27:11.728 --> 27:13.864
- I need to check you again.
- Sure.

27:15.665 --> 27:17.632
Look, I had a really good time
with you.

27:17.634 --> 27:19.671
I just wanna remember it
that way.

27:21.138 --> 27:23.208
Alright.
Look at me, please.

27:24.909 --> 27:27.743
<i>Pain, scale of one to ten,
ten is highest?</i>

27:27.745 --> 27:29.076
Uh, two.

27:29.078 --> 27:32.380
- <i>Alright. Any chills?</i>
- Um, no.

27:32.382 --> 27:34.349
- <i>Dizziness?</i>
- No.

27:34.351 --> 27:37.119
- <i>No? Headache?</i>
- Not anymore.

27:48.132 --> 27:51.033
<i>"'How about his old bunny?'
the boy's governess asked.</i>

27:51.035 --> 27:53.368
"'That, ' said the doctor.

27:53.370 --> 27:55.803
"'Why, it's a mass
of scarlet fever germs.

27:55.805 --> 27:57.605
"Burn it at once!'

27:57.607 --> 28:00.309
"And so the little rabbit
was put into a sack

28:00.311 --> 28:02.811
"with the old picture books
and a lot of rubbish

28:02.813 --> 28:06.247
"and carried out
to the end of the garden.

28:06.249 --> 28:10.252
That was a fine place
to have a bonfire."

28:10.254 --> 28:13.054
This story is sad.
Read something funny.

28:13.056 --> 28:14.790
- Yeah, funny.
- Yeah, funny.

28:14.792 --> 28:16.490
Look, this story is actually
about something.

28:16.492 --> 28:18.726
- Funny!
- Boo!

28:18.728 --> 28:21.530
- Really?
- <i>Throw it in the bonfire.</i>

28:21.532 --> 28:24.632
Alright.
I'll try this little baby here.

28:24.634 --> 28:29.204
This one is called
"Where Did My Sweet Grandma Go?"

28:29.206 --> 28:32.940
Okay. Alright, alright!
Time for a potty break, gang.

28:32.942 --> 28:34.409
Yeah, you know
what's goin' on.

28:34.411 --> 28:36.344
When we come back,
maybe Mr. Charlie will read

28:36.346 --> 28:37.813
"Walter The Farting Dog," huh?

28:37.815 --> 28:39.214
- Yeah!
- <i>Yeah!</i>

28:39.216 --> 28:40.748
- Farts! Farts! Farts!
- Farts! Farts! Farts!

28:40.750 --> 28:42.249
For your information

28:42.251 --> 28:44.553
Walter farts because
he's been fed human food.

28:44.555 --> 28:47.089
- It's actually very sad.
- This field trip sucks.

28:47.091 --> 28:50.024
Hey, whoa, whoa.
Not nice, Deangelo. Okay?

28:50.026 --> 28:52.928
Mr. Charlie's
havin' a grumpy day.

28:52.930 --> 28:54.830
Ignore him, Charlie.
His dads are gettin' a divorce.

28:54.832 --> 28:57.365
Hmm. Oh, my God.

28:57.367 --> 28:59.503
- <i>Oh, what is she doing here?</i>
- Nothing good.

29:01.238 --> 29:02.806
- What's up?
- Hey.

29:05.275 --> 29:06.611
Cool.

29:08.545 --> 29:10.014
How you doin', Charlie?

29:11.547 --> 29:14.349
- Uh..
- I... I feel terrible.

29:14.351 --> 29:15.950
You had a nice,
depressing date planned

29:15.952 --> 29:18.553
and I ruined it and made you
crack your head open.

29:18.555 --> 29:22.125
- I think you should go.
- Wait. Is everything okay?

29:24.260 --> 29:26.194
I don't know how to answer that.

29:26.196 --> 29:27.661
You're back at work.

29:27.663 --> 29:29.730
Fine,
then everything's stupendous.

29:29.732 --> 29:32.034
Look, I know,
you wanted to take things slow

29:32.036 --> 29:33.601
and I messed it up.

29:33.603 --> 29:35.137
I... I just..

29:35.139 --> 29:38.372
I think
I... I tried to get physical

29:38.374 --> 29:39.608
because I was trying to escape

29:39.610 --> 29:41.275
the emotional connection
we were having and...

29:41.277 --> 29:42.643
Fran, stop it, please?

29:42.645 --> 29:44.246
I don't wanna do this.
I can't do it.

29:44.248 --> 29:46.180
If you're looking
for a boyfriend, I'm not him.

29:46.182 --> 29:47.282
Oh, come on, Charlie,
I'm just trying to figure out

29:47.284 --> 29:48.582
why I do this thing.

29:48.584 --> 29:49.851
You wanna have fun?
You want to escape?

29:49.853 --> 29:52.023
- Look, meet my brother.
- Wait, what?

29:53.723 --> 29:55.424
I... I don't want
another relationship, Charlie.

29:55.426 --> 29:57.292
That's fine.
You won't get one.

29:57.294 --> 29:59.561
I guarantee within six weeks,
he is out of there.

29:59.563 --> 30:01.662
Six weeks is forty two days.

30:01.664 --> 30:04.167
Yes, awesome multiplication,
Frederick.

30:05.199 --> 30:05.801
You believe this kid?
Five years old.

30:05.803 --> 30:07.669
He's a hot male
kindergarten teacher.

30:07.671 --> 30:10.304
Look at that jawline.
Snap him up.

30:10.306 --> 30:12.407
Hey, Cooper, do me a favor.

30:12.409 --> 30:15.110
Take this lovely lady
out for a coffee.

30:15.112 --> 30:17.344
Tell her about the time you went
skydiving with Liza Minnelli.

30:17.346 --> 30:19.180
Correction,
it was a small Asian man

30:19.182 --> 30:20.582
who looked like Liza Minnelli.

30:20.584 --> 30:22.918
I'm so confused,
and frankly a little offended.

30:22.920 --> 30:25.187
I don't wanna get coffee
with your brother. No offense.

30:25.189 --> 30:27.389
Then go for tea or popsicles

30:27.391 --> 30:28.957
or don't go at all.
I don't care.

30:28.959 --> 30:31.161
Just, please, leave me alone.

30:38.134 --> 30:40.171
- Jeff Cho.
- What?

30:41.438 --> 30:43.772
His name was Jeff Cho.

30:45.308 --> 30:47.109
<i>Oh, man,
that was such a mistake.</i>

30:47.111 --> 30:48.743
What was I hopin' to hear?

30:48.745 --> 30:51.012
"Oh, you tried to kill me,
but that's alright. We're cool."

30:51.014 --> 30:53.148
Look, I know you feel bad.

30:53.150 --> 30:55.484
Take it from me.
Charlie's gonna be fine.

30:55.486 --> 30:57.552
He's used to this.
I've seen that guy pass out

30:57.554 --> 31:00.221
after he caught a fish, okay?

31:00.223 --> 31:01.922
One time he found a prize
at the bottom of a box

31:01.924 --> 31:03.691
of Corn Pops. Gone.

31:03.693 --> 31:06.628
Every time the Jets win,
which luckily is very rare...

31:06.630 --> 31:09.497
Oh, phew. For a second there,
I thought I was special.

31:09.499 --> 31:11.399
Oh, you know what I mean.
Come on.

31:11.401 --> 31:14.034
I do, and I am very comforted
by your insults.

31:14.036 --> 31:16.138
- Great.
- Thanks, Cooper.

31:16.140 --> 31:18.005
Is that a family name?
I've never heard that before.

31:18.007 --> 31:20.175
- Named after the dog.
- That's not true.

31:20.177 --> 31:22.511
It is true. 100%.

31:22.513 --> 31:23.844
Yeah, it was a Saint Bernard.

31:23.846 --> 31:25.213
He died
just before I was born

31:25.215 --> 31:27.849
and Charlie started
callin' me Cooper.

31:27.851 --> 31:29.383
I guess I was a hairy baby.

31:33.222 --> 31:35.258
Well, thanks for the pep talk.

31:36.994 --> 31:38.262
See you around.

31:39.830 --> 31:41.662
Hey, where are you headed?

31:41.664 --> 31:43.532
- Uh, Cobble Hill.
- That's great.

31:43.534 --> 31:45.766
That's right on our way.
We'll give you a ride.

31:45.768 --> 31:47.369
- Okay.
- Just a heads up.

31:47.371 --> 31:49.170
The ride's
a big yellow school bus.

31:49.172 --> 31:50.240
Oh.

31:51.708 --> 31:52.873
Yeah, alright. Sure.

31:52.875 --> 31:54.708
Okay. Here we go.

31:54.710 --> 31:57.946
<i>Hey, Deangelo.
I got a new bus buddy.</i>

31:57.948 --> 31:59.613
I guess she just wanted
a chance to say

31:59.615 --> 32:01.315
all the things
she didn't say to you.

32:01.317 --> 32:03.651
It was actually
kind of a word flood.

32:03.653 --> 32:05.253
Do you wanna hear?

32:05.255 --> 32:07.658
- No, not really.
- Yeah, I don't blame you.

32:09.226 --> 32:11.161
Leave it in the past.

32:15.399 --> 32:17.131
We, uh, actually ended up
hittin' it off.

32:17.133 --> 32:19.434
- <i>Yeah?</i>
- Yeah, she's a big laugher.

32:19.436 --> 32:20.936
I don't think
I'm that funny, but..

32:20.938 --> 32:22.903
Come on, you're funny.
I like your De Niro.

32:22.905 --> 32:24.374
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

32:25.441 --> 32:27.175
Oh, here we go. Here we go.

32:27.177 --> 32:30.078
- "Cape Fear."
- Do a line.

32:30.080 --> 32:31.880
I made him an offer
he couldn't refuse.

32:31.882 --> 32:34.448
- That's Brando.
- It's eventually him, right?

32:34.450 --> 32:36.051
Him before, yeah. I guess.

32:36.053 --> 32:37.552
- Kind of.
- Yeah.

32:37.554 --> 32:39.353
Do, like, uh, "Goodfellas."

32:39.355 --> 32:41.957
- "Look who's talkin' too!"
- Jesus Christ.

32:41.959 --> 32:43.891
No, I know
that one's not right.

32:43.893 --> 32:45.695
"Were you talkin' to me?"

32:47.130 --> 32:49.563
That's honestly awful.

32:49.565 --> 32:52.399
Anyway, I thought, uh..

32:52.401 --> 32:54.872
I don't know.
I might ask her out.

32:56.305 --> 32:57.706
- Francesca?
- Yeah.

32:57.708 --> 32:59.573
You know, just,
if you're cool with it.

32:59.575 --> 33:01.976
- Yeah, I'm cool with it. Yeah.
- Good, 'cause I don't wanna..

33:01.978 --> 33:03.378
No, of course, sure.
Be my guest.

33:03.380 --> 33:04.845
You two are perfect together.

33:04.847 --> 33:06.783
- You sure?
- Yeah, I said I'm sure.

33:11.388 --> 33:12.419
Alright.

33:20.863 --> 33:23.398
A can of your cheapest beer,
please.

33:23.400 --> 33:25.499
Cooper, what a nice surprise.

33:25.501 --> 33:28.269
Alright. This place is great.

33:28.271 --> 33:30.205
Looks like it hasn't changed
in 50 years.

33:30.207 --> 33:31.939
Oh, you should see what it costs
to make it look that way.

33:31.941 --> 33:33.374
Oh, yeah? Are you the owner?

33:33.376 --> 33:35.409
- Me? No.
- Oh.

33:35.411 --> 33:38.045
I'm the day manager.
You know, easy come, easy go.

33:38.047 --> 33:42.182
Oh. Still drinkin' Pabst
in this neighborhood.

33:42.184 --> 33:45.019
We get it. It's terrible.
You're hilarious!

33:46.555 --> 33:47.721
Split it with me?

33:47.723 --> 33:50.057
No, no,
I can't drink on the job.

33:50.059 --> 33:51.995
Should have been
a kindergarten teacher.

33:54.297 --> 33:56.700
Maybe, uh, maybe another time?

33:58.901 --> 34:02.704
Uh, I'm gonna take a break
from men for a while.

34:02.706 --> 34:05.340
Especially since
I almost killed the last one.

34:05.342 --> 34:07.175
Last two,
come to think of it.

34:07.177 --> 34:08.777
Well, you are in luck.

34:08.779 --> 34:11.779
I've been told
I'm very difficult to kill.

34:11.781 --> 34:14.014
I do enjoy talking to you,

34:14.016 --> 34:16.451
and, um, I do find you charming

34:16.453 --> 34:21.022
in a sort of like Saint Bernard
kind of way.

34:21.024 --> 34:23.424
- Yeah.
- But Charlie..

34:23.426 --> 34:26.460
Hey, he's the one who set us up.

34:26.462 --> 34:27.795
I checked with him
and he's cool.

34:27.797 --> 34:29.531
I wouldn't be here
if he wasn't.

34:29.533 --> 34:31.399
- Hey, Francesca?
- Yeah?

34:31.400 --> 34:33.234
Is it okay
if I take my break early?

34:33.235 --> 34:34.569
I need to call my grandmother

34:34.571 --> 34:36.571
but there's a group
of drunk bike messengers

34:36.572 --> 34:39.540
who keep yelling the word
titties in the background.

34:39.542 --> 34:41.178
Of course, sweetheart.

34:43.245 --> 34:45.112
Hi, I'm Bethany.

34:45.114 --> 34:47.614
I like your shirt.
Is it pima cotton?

34:47.616 --> 34:50.918
I, uh, don't know.

34:50.920 --> 34:53.955
Oh. You would know
if it was pima.

34:53.956 --> 34:56.991
Pima cotton feels like
baby hair.

34:56.993 --> 34:59.226
Yeah, I guess it doesn't feel
like baby hair.

34:59.228 --> 35:02.332
Must be Egyptian cotton then,
which is also nice.

35:03.500 --> 35:05.766
- Phew.
- Yeah.

35:05.768 --> 35:07.101
Whoo.

35:07.103 --> 35:08.969
Phew.

35:08.971 --> 35:10.408
Okay, bye.

35:19.248 --> 35:20.681
Hey, hear me out.

35:20.683 --> 35:22.683
Uh, how would you feel
if we set up Charlie

35:22.685 --> 35:25.085
with someone
a little more his speed?

35:25.087 --> 35:29.223
I went to a seminar last night
on the history of sandals.

35:29.225 --> 35:33.428
It was called, uh,
"Walk 10,000 Years In My Shoes."

35:33.430 --> 35:35.897
Bethany?
Sounds like the kind of girl

35:35.899 --> 35:37.598
who had her own horse
growing up.

35:37.600 --> 35:39.033
No, I... I don't know
about that.

35:39.035 --> 35:40.601
I met her at the bar
where Francesca works.

35:40.603 --> 35:43.804
She's nothing like Francesca.
She's more, uh, restrained.

35:43.806 --> 35:46.540
- Oh, like shy?
- No. No, not exactly.

35:46.542 --> 35:48.143
Just, uh, she's not real
in your face.

35:48.145 --> 35:49.777
You know, actually, she...
she's kind of hard to hear.

35:49.779 --> 35:51.212
Cooper,
you don't have to do this.

35:51.214 --> 35:53.147
You can date Francesca
without finding me a sub.

35:53.149 --> 35:55.150
I'll be honest.
It started out that way

35:55.152 --> 35:58.752
but no joke,
this chick is perfect for you.

35:58.754 --> 36:00.288
One I can picture in sweatpants?

36:00.290 --> 36:02.656
Dude,
full top to bottom sweat suit.

36:02.658 --> 36:05.826
Now that's just creepy.
I'm not sure, man.

36:05.828 --> 36:08.696
The last thing I need right now
is to get overexcited again.

36:08.698 --> 36:10.698
Yeah, bro. I don't think
that's gonna be a problem.

36:10.700 --> 36:12.035
No?

36:13.236 --> 36:15.069
Hello.

36:15.071 --> 36:16.971
I was wondering if you could
point me to the section

36:16.973 --> 36:19.140
of your library
dealing with amaranth?

36:19.142 --> 36:21.609
Amaranth, the grain?

36:21.611 --> 36:23.111
Yes.

36:23.113 --> 36:26.214
The ancient grain
cultivated by the Aztecs

36:26.216 --> 36:28.116
<i>now enjoying
a quinoa-like comeback</i>

36:28.118 --> 36:30.654
thanks to its high protein
content and nutty flavor.

36:33.989 --> 36:35.993
- Uh, sure. Right this way.
- Okay.

36:39.196 --> 36:40.828
Ah, here.

36:40.830 --> 36:43.200
"Amaranth And You."

36:44.433 --> 36:46.667
It seems to have a lot of..

36:46.669 --> 36:49.506
...historical information
as well as recipes.

36:51.942 --> 36:54.442
- Thanks, Charlie.
- You're welcome. What?

36:54.444 --> 36:56.911
- Oh. Ah, I'm Bethany.
- Oh.

36:56.913 --> 36:58.580
<i>They said
we'd have a lot in common.</i>

36:58.582 --> 37:01.549
Right.
I guess they were right.

37:01.551 --> 37:04.118
- 'Cause you like books.
- Yeah.

37:04.120 --> 37:06.520
Yeah, I love them.

37:06.522 --> 37:07.955
I love the smell of them.

37:07.957 --> 37:09.123
- Mm-hmm.
- The old books.

37:09.125 --> 37:11.458
Yeah, that, you know,
that's called furfural.

37:11.460 --> 37:12.726
- Furfural?
- Yeah.

37:12.728 --> 37:14.828
- Oh.
- And furfural and vanillin.

37:14.830 --> 37:17.632
It's like, uh,
they're volatile compounds

37:17.634 --> 37:20.534
released by, uh,
decomposing paper and glue.

37:20.536 --> 37:23.437
There's probably some mold
in there as well.

37:23.439 --> 37:25.440
Some people find it
very, uh, you know...

37:25.442 --> 37:26.975
- Romantic.
- Romantic, yeah.

37:26.977 --> 37:28.112
Yeah.

37:30.446 --> 37:31.515
Oh.

37:38.254 --> 37:41.388
So, um, how does
amaranth and chickpeas

37:41.390 --> 37:43.326
with spring lamb sound?

37:45.995 --> 37:48.429
- Are you asking me out?
- No.

37:48.431 --> 37:50.698
No, I... I was just asking

37:50.700 --> 37:53.870
if that's something I should
make if you asked me out.

37:56.205 --> 37:59.473
Alright. Bethany, would you
like to go out some time?

37:59.475 --> 38:00.577
Oh.

38:07.683 --> 38:09.250
Okay.

38:09.252 --> 38:10.951
Good.

38:10.953 --> 38:13.154
Friday?

38:13.156 --> 38:15.455
Friday
I have yarn-making class.

38:15.457 --> 38:18.393
I'd skip it, but we're about
to take on alpaca, so..

38:18.395 --> 38:21.029
Oh, yeah. Uh, Saturday?

38:21.031 --> 38:22.733
- Saturday's great.
- Yeah.

38:24.466 --> 38:26.433
I'll make amaranth.

38:26.435 --> 38:28.303
- Look..
- Please.

38:28.305 --> 38:29.636
I like her.

38:29.638 --> 38:32.105
She's pleasant.

38:32.107 --> 38:34.007
Yeah. Yeah, that's exactly
what she is.

38:34.009 --> 38:35.143
- She's pleasant.
- Right?

38:35.145 --> 38:36.476
I met her, I said

38:36.478 --> 38:38.379
"My God,
that is one pleasant girl."

38:38.381 --> 38:40.417
Yeah,
so we'll see how that goes.

38:42.319 --> 38:43.618
You goin' out with Francesca?

38:43.620 --> 38:45.719
Ooh, Mr. Cooper's
got a girlfriend.

38:45.721 --> 38:47.388
- Muah, muah, muah.
- Muah, muah, muah.

38:47.390 --> 38:49.991
Alright. You know
I don't like labels, Deangelo.

38:49.993 --> 38:51.558
You all know that.

38:51.560 --> 38:53.995
And, yes, I am going out
with Miss Francesca

38:53.997 --> 38:55.996
on Saturday night.

38:55.998 --> 38:57.598
Though where, I don't know.

38:57.600 --> 38:59.667
You gotta help me out.
What's this chick like to do?

38:59.669 --> 39:01.902
Don't ask me.
You're the one dating her.

39:01.904 --> 39:04.374
- You set us up.
- Technically, sure.

39:05.875 --> 39:07.908
Look, she's intimidating, okay?

39:07.910 --> 39:09.509
I feel like

39:09.511 --> 39:11.346
sometimes we're havin'
three conversations at once

39:11.348 --> 39:13.982
and I can't follow
one of them, you know.

39:13.984 --> 39:15.650
Alright, look, I know
she's really into Bauhaus.

39:15.652 --> 39:19.786
There's an Oskar Schlemmer
retrospective right now at MoMA.

39:19.788 --> 39:21.755
That's exactly
what I'm talkin' about.

39:21.757 --> 39:25.225
I need somethin' fun.
I need a good distraction.

39:25.227 --> 39:28.895
It doesn't take much
and this chick... goes dark.

39:28.897 --> 39:31.132
Yeah, Cooper, she's having
a tough time with her aunt.

39:31.134 --> 39:33.801
I know. I know,
and it's super sad. It is.

39:33.803 --> 39:35.870
So let's stop talkin' about it
already.

39:35.872 --> 39:37.371
I need to pee-pee.

39:37.373 --> 39:39.239
Yeah, you and me both,
Frederick.

39:39.241 --> 39:40.674
Alright, come on, guys.
Pick up the pace.

39:40.676 --> 39:42.609
High knees, huh? Let's go.

39:42.611 --> 39:44.547
How about just going somewhere..

39:47.216 --> 39:49.049
...uh, noisy?

39:51.721 --> 39:54.321
- How's your pisco sour?
- What?

39:54.323 --> 39:56.857
The pisco sour. Good?

39:56.859 --> 39:59.993
Only for about six months.

39:59.995 --> 40:02.429
Before that,
I was in San Francisco.

40:02.431 --> 40:03.634
Have you been?

40:05.035 --> 40:07.467
It's so good.

40:07.469 --> 40:10.071
Yeah, so tangy.

40:10.073 --> 40:11.906
♪ Hey-yah ♪♪

40:14.176 --> 40:15.877
No one saw it coming.

40:15.879 --> 40:18.612
Here everyone had psyched
themselves up for alpaca

40:18.614 --> 40:21.482
and the teacher breaks out
yak wool.

40:21.484 --> 40:22.917
One guy had to take a time out.

40:22.919 --> 40:25.152
Oh, sounds intense.
Thank you.

40:25.154 --> 40:26.788
Crazy intense.

40:26.790 --> 40:30.357
I guess from now on, I better
not get too comfortable.

40:30.359 --> 40:32.296
Not if you know
what's good for you.

40:34.163 --> 40:38.132
So, this is, um,
amaranth and chickpeas.

40:38.134 --> 40:41.301
But no lamb.
Sorry, I... I felt bad.

40:41.303 --> 40:42.937
Oh, no. That's... that's fine.

40:42.939 --> 40:45.205
It looks amazing.
Thank you so much for cooking.

40:45.207 --> 40:47.208
Oh, you're welcome.

40:47.210 --> 40:49.576
I like to cook
in other people's kitchens.

40:49.578 --> 40:52.179
It's like a little window
into their souls.

40:52.181 --> 40:54.949
Ah, what did you see in mine?

40:54.951 --> 40:57.118
Extremely dull knives.

40:57.120 --> 40:59.589
That's more accurate
than you'll ever know.

41:01.190 --> 41:03.292
Mm! It's good.

41:05.060 --> 41:06.794
- Do you have kids?
- What? No.

41:06.796 --> 41:08.196
No, why... why would you..

41:08.198 --> 41:09.996
I saw you have some foam

41:09.998 --> 41:12.833
<i>taped to the corner
of that table over there.</i>

41:12.835 --> 41:14.402
<i>Well, that's just what
my sister does</i>

41:14.404 --> 41:16.237
<i>for her son
who's learning to walk.</i>

41:16.239 --> 41:19.005
- Goddammit.
- Oh.

41:19.007 --> 41:22.379
- I don't mind kids, so..
- It's not that, Bethany.

41:24.413 --> 41:26.813
Alright, there's something
you deserve to know.

41:26.815 --> 41:29.650
I have cataplexy which means
that I can pass out

41:29.652 --> 41:33.788
any time I feel strong emotions.

41:33.790 --> 41:35.323
Strong emotions?

41:35.325 --> 41:36.457
- Like what do you...
- <i>It could be anything.</i>

41:36.459 --> 41:39.092
Like fear, anger, surprise,
all of that.

41:39.094 --> 41:41.098
In my case, it's mainly..

41:42.531 --> 41:44.632
It's mainly joy.

41:44.634 --> 41:47.368
Oh. That's horrible.

41:47.370 --> 41:49.837
Yeah, it's not great,
but listen

41:49.839 --> 41:52.339
there's nothing
saying I can't feel

41:52.341 --> 41:54.674
mild, tepid emotions.

41:54.676 --> 41:57.044
I can go to town on those.

41:57.046 --> 41:58.478
Oh, gosh.

41:58.480 --> 42:00.817
Did I get you too worked up
about the yarn?

42:03.386 --> 42:04.654
Um, nope.

42:05.989 --> 42:08.022
I guess we all have
something weird about us.

42:08.024 --> 42:09.556
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

42:09.558 --> 42:11.828
I'm sexually attracted
to Bob Newhart.

42:18.968 --> 42:20.967
- What?
- "Rock Lobster!"

42:22.205 --> 42:23.538
- Come on!
- Okay!

42:23.540 --> 42:25.172
"Rock Lobster!"

42:25.174 --> 42:27.741
- ♪ Ooh ♪
- ♪ We were at a party ♪

42:27.743 --> 42:31.145
- ♪ Ooh ♪
- ♪ His earlobe fell in the deep ♪

42:31.147 --> 42:32.946
♪ Someone reached in
and grabbed it ♪

42:32.948 --> 42:36.250
- ♪ Ooh ♪
- ♪ It was a rock lobster ♪

42:36.252 --> 42:41.221
♪ Ahh ahh ahh ahh ♪

42:41.223 --> 42:46.963
- ♪ Rock lobster ♪
- ♪ Ahh ahh ahh ahh ♪♪

42:52.000 --> 42:55.536
I brought over some movies,
but now I'm wondering.

42:55.538 --> 42:57.504
Have you seen "Secret Of NIMH?"

42:57.506 --> 42:59.707
I was such a basket case
at the end of that.

42:59.709 --> 43:02.176
I think I'll be okay.

43:02.178 --> 43:04.114
I'm sitting down already.

43:05.747 --> 43:07.683
I think
we should play it safe.

43:12.288 --> 43:13.390
Oh, hey.

43:15.892 --> 43:18.259
<i>We have shared
the incommunicable</i>

43:18.261 --> 43:20.962
<i>experience of war.</i>

43:20.964 --> 43:23.964
<i>In our youths, our hearts
were touched with fire.</i>

43:23.966 --> 43:26.433
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪

43:26.435 --> 43:29.036
<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪</i>

43:29.038 --> 43:31.739
<i>♪ Ooh-ooh ooh-ooh
ooh-ooh ooh-ooh ♪</i>

43:31.741 --> 43:34.408
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh
ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪♪

43:34.410 --> 43:37.879
<i>The Civil War was fought
in 10,000 places</i>

43:37.881 --> 43:41.549
<i>from Valverde, New Mexico,
and Tullahoma, Tennessee</i>

43:41.551 --> 43:43.451
<i>to Saint Albans, Vermont</i>

43:43.453 --> 43:45.756
<i>and Fernandina
on the Florida coast.</i>

43:47.924 --> 43:50.123
<i>More than three million
Americans fought in it..</i>

43:50.125 --> 43:53.661
This is nice.
I feel really comfortable.

43:53.663 --> 43:55.897
<i>Two percent of the population
died in it.</i>

43:55.899 --> 43:57.601
Yeah, me too.

43:59.134 --> 44:02.169
<i>American churches
sheltered the dying..</i>

44:02.171 --> 44:03.904
- Ah.
- Whoo!

44:03.906 --> 44:07.375
Uh, let me get you a cab.
Or we could share?

44:07.377 --> 44:09.880
- You know, just..
- Hold on, it's my aunt.

44:10.879 --> 44:12.279
Is she waitin' up for you?

44:12.281 --> 44:14.781
Not waiting up.
More like throwing up.

44:14.783 --> 44:16.683
Oh, shit.

44:16.685 --> 44:18.219
Um, alright.

44:18.221 --> 44:21.288
Come back to my place,
open a bottle of wine.

44:21.290 --> 44:24.093
- I can't. I gotta check on her.
- Of course.

44:25.560 --> 44:28.431
Uh, you know, I could help.

44:29.598 --> 44:31.232
- Don't worry about it.
- Okay.

44:31.234 --> 44:33.333
Um, and besides,
I'd like to keep this separate.

44:33.335 --> 44:35.803
- Us separate, if that's okay.
- Yeah.

44:35.805 --> 44:37.971
Hey, think of me
as your... your weekend escape.

44:37.973 --> 44:40.507
- <i>Okay.</i>
- Uh, also free weekdays, so..

44:40.509 --> 44:42.812
But no pressure. Um..

44:45.480 --> 44:47.417
I'll probably just walk it.

44:58.294 --> 45:00.460
What are you..

45:00.462 --> 45:02.996
Ah, crap, this hurts.
How far am I?

45:02.998 --> 45:06.299
...your knee is facing up
and your toes are facing in.

45:06.301 --> 45:08.601
- About 3 feet.
- Oh.

45:08.603 --> 45:12.005
This girl says she can teach you
to do the splits in a day.

45:12.007 --> 45:13.741
That girl is nine years old,
Sylvia.

